"16oz can poured into pint glass. Pours a cola brown with fizzy head that disappears rapidly. The nose is heavy roasted coffee with a touch of oatmeal and biscuit, not a whole lot else. The taste is similar. Pretty one dimensional, heavy coffee roast, a bit of cream and not much else. Wish there was more of a malt backbone here. The oatmeal is definitely present and brings a cream like component to the beer. The mouthfeel is light and highly carbonated. This is an easy drinking coffee stout. This would be a good ""summer stout"" as it features some nice roasty flavors but drinks very light and is refreshing."
